<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-02-03T16:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-02-03T16:30:00-05:00" n="443" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d443">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/994: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Venezuela</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Caracas</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-02-03T17:00:00-04:30">February 3, 1933—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 7:12 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2. Department’s circular telegram February 1, 7 p.m. The Foreign Office
                            states that it is now sending a telegram to Peru supporting the position
                            taken by the Department.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>